"""
Diverse SNN Triage System (N=2)
===============================
Two noise-trained diverse SNNs as cheap gate + ANN escalation on disagreement.

Builds on findings from the ensemble emergence experiments:
- Membrane noise improves SNN accuracy (+5%), sparsity (-25%), diversity (-10% corr)
- N=2 is the cost-optimal ensemble size (0.60x before triage)
- Disagreement between diverse SNNs is a better difficulty signal than single-SNN confidence
- Soft voting recovers second-choice agreement on ambiguous inputs

Architecture:
  Input → Both SNNs process (parallel, 0.60x cost)
    → Agree? → Return soft-vote answer (cheap path)
    → Disagree? → Escalate to ANN (expensive path, 1.0x cost)

Baselines compared:
  A) ANN only (1.0x cost, ~90.7% accuracy)
  B) Single SNN only (0.30x cost, ~88.8% accuracy)
  C) Single SNN + ANN triage (original hybrid from prior research)
  D) N=2 diverse SNN soft vote, no triage (0.60x cost)
  E) N=2 diverse SNN + ANN triage (the new architecture)

Run: Google Colab, GPU runtime.
"""

import torch
import torch.nn as nn
import torch.nn.functional as F
from torch.utils.data import DataLoader
